<TITLE> Stocks close down on market corrections </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 07 (bdnews24.com)Bourses continued to slide Monday amid investor sell-offs mostly in banks. Analysts see the steady fall in indices this week as a sign of price corrections, leading to market stability. "The rise in indices the previous week posed a threat of the market becoming overheated and issues being overvalued. However, the fall this week led to price corrections and kept the market stable," Dhaka Stock Exchange's chief executive Salahuddin Ahmed told bdnews24.com. Investors opted for issues of insurers, mutual funds and power companies over the day, according to brokerage house officials. The benchmark DGEN or general index ended at 3040.59, losing 22.54 points or 0.73 percent. The DSI or all-share price index fell 18.71 points or 0.72 percent to 2559.31. The bourse's blue-chip DSE-20 ended down 15.17 points or 0.65 percent to 2316.15. Turnover rose to Tk 3.06 billion from Sunday's Tk 2.89 billion, on the trading of 28,109,658 shares. Losers outnumbered gainers 157 to 85 and eight issues remained unchanged. The day's trade was paced by issues in banks and financial institutions, pharmaceuticals, mutual funds, insurers and power companies. Square Pharma topped the turnover board, closing at Tk 4483 up 2.63 percent. AIMS 1st mutual fund continued to gain from Sunday, rising 1.11 percent to Tk 11.83. Banking heavyweight AB Bank continued to decline, finishing at Tk 3448 down 0.29 percent. IFIC Bank fell 1.25 percent to end on Tk 2904. Uttara Bank eroded Sunday's losses and advanced 0.23 percent to Tk 5631.50. Among the other scrips on the turnover board  Grameen Mutual Fund One, Union Capitals and Power Grid Company of Bangladesh also gained. Beximco Pharma and Lanka Bangla Finance fell on profit taking following gains the previous day. All the indices on the Chittagong Stock Exchange ended down influenced by falls in banks and cements. Insurers, mutual funds and financial institutions enjoyed the largest gains. The CSCX or selective categories index closed at 5456.34, down 81.78 points or 1.48 percent. The CASPI or all-share price index slid 118.06 points or 1.38 percent to end on 8426.98. The CSE-30 blue-chip index lost 93.14 points or 1.25 percent to 7324.59. The port city bourse's turnover increased to Tk 462.43 million from Tk 453.01 million the previous day through 4,998,695 shares changing hands. Of the traded issues, 43 advanced, 98 declined and five held steady. bdn
